## Name Construction (με λένε)

<pattern name="name-construction" color="ocean">
<title>Name Construction</title>
<subtitle>με λένε = my name is (lit. "they call me")</subtitle>

<principle>
[Pronoun] λένε + name - literally "they call me..."
</principle>

| Greek              | English                    |
|--------------------|----------------------------|
| Με λένε...         | My name is... (they call me) |
| Σε λένε...         | Your name is...            |
| Τον/Την λένε...    | His/Her name is...         |
| Πώς σε λένε;       | What's your name?          |

</pattern>

---

## Pattern Logic

<insight>
Both constructions flip the English perspective:

**"I like coffee"** → Literally: "To-me is-pleasing the-coffee"
- μου = to me (indirect object)
- αρέσει = is pleasing (verb agrees with coffee!)
- ο καφές = the coffee (subject)

**"My name is..."** → Literally: "They call me..."
- με = me (object)
- λένε = they call (3rd person plural)
- The "they" is impersonal

</insight>

